Papilio canadensis is a species of butterfly commonly known as the Canadian tiger swallowtail. 
Its wingspan measures between 7 and 10 cm. 
The upper side of their wings is predominantly yellow with black markings and blue and orange spots. 
The underside of the wings is yellow with black markings and a row of blue and orange spots. 
Papilio canadensis can be found in various habitats, including deciduous and coniferous forests, along streams and in open meadows. 
They typically feed on nectar from a variety of flowers. 
Papilio canadensis is a common and widely distributed species throughout North America.
